---
import LegalLayout from '../../../layouts/LegalLayout.astro'
import { APPS, LAST_UPDATED, SUPPORT_EMAIL } from '../../../legal-config'

const app = APPS[0]
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  appName={app.name}
  lastUpdated={LAST_UPDATED}
  description="How Wardrobe Studio handles app data, photos, account information, purchases, location, and support requests."
>
  <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how Wardrobe Studio handles information when you use the app. Wardrobe Studio is
    designed as a personal wardrobe, outfit planning, wishlist, and style-tracking app. This page is
    a practical transparency document and does not replace professional legal advice.
  </p>
  <p>
    Wardrobe Studio is developed and maintained by Nacho Martínez, operating under the Sizle Digital
    Product Studio brand.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>
    Wardrobe Studio stores the following information when you choose to add or create it: wardrobe items,
    item names, categories, brands, colors, notes, barcodes, purchase prices, wishlist target
    prices, product links, photos of clothing, outfits, wear logs, style preferences, trip plans,
    destination names, dates, recommendation feedback, notification preferences, and profile details
    such as name, email, birthday, avatar symbol, and optional profile photo.
  </p>
  <p>
    Wardrobe Studio may process the following information only when you enable or use the related feature:
    location, camera access, photo library access, notifications, widgets, backups, purchases,
    account-related information, and product information shared through the Safari share extension.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you create or sign in to an account, Wardrobe Studio may process account information such as email
    address, authentication status, and a provider user identifier. Passwords and verification flows
    are handled by the authentication provider rather than being stored directly by Wardrobe Studio.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you use Sign in with Apple, Apple may provide Wardrobe Studio with your name, email address, private
    relay email address, and provider identifier depending on your Apple ID choices. This
    information is used to create or access your Wardrobe Studio account and to provide account-related
    functionality.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you use the Safari share extension, Wardrobe Studio may temporarily store product information from
    the page you shared, such as product URL, suggested name, brand, image URL, price text, currency,
    color, and capture time. This is used to prefill wishlist items.
  </p>

  <h2>3. How We Use Information</h2>
  <p>
    Wardrobe Studio uses information to save your wardrobe, build outfit suggestions, track wears, maintain
    wishlist items, generate style statistics, personalize weather-aware recommendations, prepare
    trip outfit plans, show widgets, schedule reminders you enable, manage account access, process
    Pro entitlements, respond to support requests, and maintain app reliability.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Local Storage, Backups, and Shared App Data</h2>
  <p>
    Most wardrobe content is stored locally on your device unless a sync, account, backup, or
    backend-backed feature explicitly sends that data to a provider. The app also uses an Apple App
    Group to share limited data with the widget and share extension, such as the look-of-the-day
    cache, widget thumbnails, and pending wishlist share payloads.
  </p>
  <p>
    Exported backup files may include wardrobe data, notes, outfit information, wishlist entries,
    and photos if included in the export. Anyone with access to an exported backup file may be able
    to view the information contained in it. Keep exported backups in a safe location and avoid
    sharing them with people you do not trust.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Permissions and Device Features</h2>
  <p>
    Wardrobe Studio may request access to your photo library so you can choose garment and profile photos,
    camera access so you can scan barcodes or capture item-related content, and notification
    permission so reminders and planning nudges can be scheduled. You can manage these permissions
    in iOS Settings.
  </p>
  <p>
    Location is used to provide local weather-aware recommendations when you grant permission. You
    can deny location access and continue using Wardrobe Studio, although some weather-aware or
    location-based features may be limited or require manual configuration where available.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>
    Wardrobe Studio uses Apple services such as StoreKit for purchases and subscriptions, WeatherKit for
    weather-aware recommendations, Photos, Camera, Notifications, Widgets, and App Groups where
    enabled by the operating system.
  </p>
  <p>
    Weather information may be provided using Apple Weather where available. Weather data
    attribution and source information should be displayed in the app where weather data is shown.
  </p>
  <p>
    Firebase may be used for authentication and account management. Wardrobe Studio content is not uploaded
    to Firebase unless a sync or backend-backed feature clearly indicates that it will store that
    content remotely. Firebase Analytics is disabled in the app configuration covered by this
    policy. If analytics are enabled in the future, this policy and the App Store privacy details
    will be updated before or alongside that change.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you use the share extension or product image preview features, Wardrobe Studio may request image
    data from the product URL or image URL associated with the page you shared.
  </p>
  <p>
    Wardrobe Studio does not use third-party advertising SDKs and does not sell personal information.
    Wardrobe Studio does not use your data to track you across apps or websites owned by other companies.
  </p>

  <h2>7. In-App Purchases and Subscriptions</h2>
  <p>
    Wardrobe Studio may offer Pro features through monthly, yearly, or lifetime in-app purchases. Purchases
    and subscriptions are processed through Apple&apos;s App Store using StoreKit. Apple handles
    payment details, billing, subscription management, cancellations, and refund requests. Wardrobe Studio
    receives purchase entitlement information, such as product identifiers and transaction status,
    but does not receive full payment card details.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Data Retention</h2>
  <p>
    Local wardrobe data remains on your device until you delete it, delete your account from within
    the app where available, uninstall the app, reset the device, or otherwise remove the data.
    Manual backup files remain wherever you choose to store them until you delete them.
  </p>
  <p>
    Account, purchase, and provider-side technical data may be retained by Apple, Firebase, or other
    involved service providers according to their own policies and legal obligations.
  </p>

  <h2>9. User Rights and Privacy Requests</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, export, restrict, or
    object to certain uses of personal information. You can delete local wardrobe content in the app
    and, where account deletion is available, request deletion of the remote account from the app.
    You can also contact us for privacy requests using the email below.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Security</h2>
  <p>
    Wardrobe Studio relies on Apple platform security, local device protections, and provider security
    controls for account and purchase services. No method of storage or transmission is completely
    secure, so you should protect your device, Apple ID, and any exported backup files.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Children&apos;s Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    Wardrobe Studio is not directed to children under the age where parental consent is required by
    applicable law. If you believe a child has provided personal information through Wardrobe Studio,
    contact us so we can review the request.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. The latest version will be posted on this
    page with an updated date.
  </p>

  <h2>13. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For privacy questions, data requests, or deletion requests, contact <a
      href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a
    >.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
